  "text": "LibreOffice Core Document Model Architecture - Key Files\n\nThe LibreOffice document framework is built on a hierarchy of document shell classes, all inheriting from SfxObjectShell, which is the base document shell class defined in include/sfx2/objsh.hxx (line 182). This class serves as the common interface for all document types in the framework.\n\nEach LibreOffice application implements its own document model:\n\n1. **SfxObjectShell** (include/sfx2/objsh.hxx, line 182)\n   - The base document shell class that all document types inherit from\n   - Provides the fundamental framework for document management, loading, saving, and lifecycle\n   - Located in the core SFX2 framework library\n\n2. **SwDoc** (sw/inc/doc.hxx, line 196)\n   - The Writer (word processor) document model class\n   - Represents the central document model for word processing\n   - Defined as \"class SwDoc final\" indicating it cannot be subclassed\n   - Contains the document nodes, attributes, and all word processing logic\n\n3. **ScDocument** (sc/inc/document.hxx, line 331)\n   - The Calc (spreadsheet) document model class\n   - Manages all spreadsheet data, cells, formulas, and calculations\n   - Defined as \"class ScDocument\" as the central data structure for spreadsheet operations\n\n4. **SdDrawDocument** (sd/inc/drawdoc.hxx, line 338)\n   - The Impress/Draw document model class\n   - Inherits from FmFormModel to support drawing and form objects\n   - Defined as \"class SD_DLLPUBLIC SdDrawDocument final : public FmFormModel\"\n   - Manages slides, drawings, shapes, and presentation objects\n\n5. **SfxApplication** (include/sfx2/app.hxx, line 103)\n   - The LibreOffice application framework entry point\n   - Defined as \"class SFX2_DLLPUBLIC SfxApplication final : public SfxShell\"\n   - Manages the global application state, modules, and coordinates the framework\n   - One instance exists for the entire application lifetime\n\nThese classes form the backbone of the LibreOffice document model architecture. Each document type (Writer, Calc, Impress, Draw) builds upon the SfxObjectShell framework to provide application-specific document handling while maintaining compatibility with the core framework."
